div.p:
But then as in Jeremiah, ſo may God now ſay of this Land, I hearkned and heard, but they ſpake not aright; 
               Jer. 8▪ 6. 
               no man repented him of his wickedneſſe, ſaying, What have I done? every one turned to his courſe, as the horſe ruſheth into the Battell: Fearleſſe, and venturous in ſin ſtill. What one perſon (almoſt) in this great Congregation, hath (ſince all our calamities) left one ſin? yet this is the fear of the Lord (this is a true character of it) To depart from evil. A man durſt not continue in a courſe which provokes God, if he did truely fear God.
